The '''Green Card Test''' ('''GCT''') is a criterion used by the [[Internal Revenue Service]] (IRS) in the [[United States]] to determine whether an individual qualifies as a "resident for tax purposes". The GCT is used alongside the [[Substantial Presence Test]]. Specifically, an alien is considered a "resident for tax purposes" if they pass either the GCT or the Substantial Presence Test.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.irs.gov/Individuals/International-Taxpayers/The-Green-Card-Test-and-the-Substantial-Presence-Test |title=The Green Card Test and the Substantial Presence Test |accessdate=January 4, 2016 |publisher=Internal Revenue Service}}</ref>



