===Residency for tax purposes does not imply permanent residency===

It is possible to be a resident for tax purposes in the United States but to ''not'' be a permanent resident of the United States. A non-citizen can be a permanent resident of the United States only if he/she holds a [[United States Permanent Resident Card|Green Card]]. On the other hand, people on non-immigrant visas may well be treated as residents for tax purposes.

